  date: "October 4, 2025",
  image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1532996122724-e3c354a0b15b?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop",
  excerpt: "We need to fundamentally change the Take (extract) â†’ Make (product) â†’ Dispose (waste) system. The Circular Economy is a revolutionary idea designed to solve the waste problem at its root.",
  content: ["Design Out Waste", "Companies make products that are guaranteed to last and can be completely disassembled and remade. This means products are designed from the beginning with their entire lifecycle in mindâ€”not just how they'll be used, but how they'll be repaired, upgraded, and eventually returned to the manufacturing cycle.", "Your Action - Demand Durability: Support brands that offer lifetime warranties or repair services. Vote with your wallet by choosing companies that prioritize longevity over planned obsolescence. Look for products with modular designs that can be easily repaired and upgraded.", "When you buy a product designed to last decades instead of years, you're supporting a fundamental shift in how things are made. Companies that offer repair programs, spare parts, and upgrade options are demonstrating their commitment to circularity.", "Circulate Value", "Products are repaired and reused constantly, keeping materials in the economy for as long as possible. Instead of extracting new raw materials, we maximize the use of existing materials by keeping them in circulation through repair, refurbishment, and remanufacturing.", "Your Action - Fix It: Don't replaceâ€”repair! Support local businesses that specialize in fixing things. Learn basic repair skills yourself through online tutorials and community repair workshops. Share your repair successes to inspire others.", "Every time you repair instead of replace, you're keeping valuable materials out of the waste stream and reducing demand for new production. The circular economy only works if we, as consumers, actively participate by choosing repair over disposal and supporting businesses that make repair possible and affordable."]
